  "_ai_insights": {
    "EXEC_SUMMARY_GOOD": "JCB has achieved impressive reach with 3,080 active Copilot users across all 8 business units, growing 35% in just three months. Users explore an average of 11.5 Microsoft 365 apps — a Frontier-level breadth that signals genuine integration into workflows. Month-over-month retention holds strong at 79%, showing that once users engage, most come back.",
    "EXEC_SUMMARY_GAP": "Despite broad reach, only 8.3% of licensed users and 8.2% of chat users are habitual (11+ active days per month). With 58.3% of users active just 1–5 days monthly, most employees are experimenting but not embedding Copilot into daily routines. Additionally, 484 of 1,658 licensed seats remain inactive — representing unrealised productivity value.",
    "EXEC_SUMMARY_OPP": "JCB's 3.2× engagement premium proves that licensed users generate 71.8 prompts versus 22.8 for unlicensed — licensing drives depth. Reassigning the 484 inactive licences to the highest-engaged unlicensed users in Operations (325 unlicensed), HR (324), and Support (317) could immediately convert reach into habit and unlock significant productivity gains.",
    "INSIGHT_REACH": "JCB has scaled Copilot to 3,080 active users — 70.8% of its 1,658 licensed seats are active, with an additional 1,906 unlicensed chat users expanding the footprint. Growth has been rapid: the user base grew 35% from March (2,282) to May (3,080). All 8 business units are participating, with Operations (239 users), Marketing (237), and HR (234) leading in user counts. Agent adoption remains early at 4.3%, with 116 users across 25 deployed agents.",
    "INSIGHT_HABIT": "Habitual use is JCB's clearest growth opportunity. Only 8.3% of licensed users and 8.2% of chat users reach 11+ active days per month, placing the organisation firmly in the Foundation tier for habit formation. The active-day distribution tells the story: 58.3% of users log just 1–5 days, while only 8.2% reach 16+ days. The positive signal is that the trend is improving — the 1–5 day band dropped from 70% in March to 58% in May, suggesting users are gradually deepening engagement.",
    "INSIGHT_SKILL": "JCB users demonstrate advanced exploration with 11.5 apps per user — well above the Frontier threshold of 7. Agent users interact with 4.4 agents on average, also at Frontier level. However, agent creation remains limited at 0.9% of users, and agent habitual use sits at just 0.9%. The 79% agent return rate is encouraging, showing that users who try agents tend to come back for more.",
    "TITLE_REACH": "Broad Adoption Across All Business Units",
    "TITLE_HABIT": "Frequency Lags Behind Rapid Reach",
    "TITLE_SKILL": "Deep App Breadth, Early Agent Creation",
    "TITLE_VALUE": "Licensing Multiplies Engagement 3.2×",
    "SUBTITLE_REACH": "3,080 users across 8 orgs with 35% quarterly growth",
    "SUBTITLE_HABIT": "Only 8.3% of users reach habitual use at 11+ days per month",
    "SUBTITLE_SKILL": "11.5 apps per user with 25 agents deployed and 79% return rate",
    "SUBTITLE_VALUE": "Licensed users average 71.8 prompts versus 22.8 for unlicensed",
    "SPOTLIGHT_HABIT": "JCB's habit gap sits at the heart of its maturity challenge. While 3,080 users have tried Copilot, the active-day distribution shows most engagement remains light: 58.3% of users are active just 1–5 days per month, and only 20.9% (combining the 11–15 and 16+ day bands) qualify as habitual. The month-over-month trend is encouraging — the 1–5 day band shrank from 70% in March to 58% in May for both licensed and unlicensed tiers. Converting the 396 users in the 6–10 day band into habitual users is the highest-leverage action: these users already engage regularly and are closest to forming embedded habits.",
    "SPOTLIGHT_MATURITY": "JCB sits firmly in the Expansion pattern — strong Reach and Skill signals balanced against a Foundation-level Habit signal. The organisation has passed the awareness stage: users explore broadly (11.5 apps) and retention is solid at 79%. The bottleneck is frequency. With only 8.3% reaching habitual use and a 3.2× engagement premium for licensed users, the path to Frontier requires targeted interventions: activating the 484 idle licences, converting 6–10 day users to habitual, and scaling agent adoption beyond the current 4.3%.",
    "PULLQUOTE_0": "3,080 users in just three months signals organisation-wide momentum — now the focus shifts from reach to rhythm.",
    "PULLQUOTE_1": "All 8 business units are active, with 35% user growth from March to May.",
    "PULLQUOTE_2": "58% of users engage 5 days or fewer — converting the 396 users in the 6–10 day band is the fastest path to habit.",
    "PULLQUOTE_3": "Users explore 11.5 apps on average — Frontier-level breadth that shows Copilot is weaving into real workflows.",
    "PULLQUOTE_4": "Licensed users generate 3.2× more prompts, proving that licensing is not just access — it is activation.",
    "PULLQUOTE_5": "JCB's foundation is strong. The next chapter is turning 3,080 experimenters into habitual users.",
    "REC_1_TITLE": "Reactivate 484 Idle Licences",
    "REC_1_DESC": "484 of 1,658 licensed seats are currently inactive. Identify these users, pair them with department champions from IT (8.3 avg active days) or Sales (7.9 days), and run a 30-day activation campaign. Each activated licence represents approximately 72 prompts per month in potential productivity.",
    "REC_2_TITLE": "Launch a Habit-Building Sprint for the 6–10 Day Cohort",
    "REC_2_DESC": "The 396 users active 6–10 days per month are closest to habitual use. Target this cohort with workflow-specific use cases, weekly challenges, and prompt-of-the-day nudges. Moving half of this group to 11+ days would nearly double JCB's habitual rate from 8.3% to over 15%.",
    "REC_3_TITLE": "Scale Agent Adoption in Operations and HR",
    "REC_3_DESC": "With only 4.3% agent adoption, JCB's 25 deployed agents are underutilised. The Researcher agent (21 users, 2,066 sessions) and Visual Creator (99 users) show strong fit. Promote these proven agents to Operations (239 users, 5.4 avg days) and HR (234 users, 7.7 avg days), where high user counts and moderate engagement suggest room for workflow automation.",
    "REC_4_TITLE": "License High-Engagement Unlicensed Users",
    "REC_4_DESC": "With 1,906 unlicensed users generating only 22.8 prompts versus 71.8 for licensed, the 3.2× premium makes a clear business case. Prioritise licensing for Support (317 unlicensed, 1.8× ratio) and Operations (325 unlicensed, 1.6× ratio), starting with users already in the 6+ active-day bands."
  },
